radiographic_examinations.findings: No abnormally dilated loops of large or small bowel. Residual enteric contrast material seen within the colon. Excreted contrast also opacifies the bladder. No free intraperitoneal air. A new right lower quadrant drainage catheter is noted. Innumerable surgical clips are seen over the abdomen and pelvis. Rounded mineralized densities projecting over the right upper quadrant likely reflect cholelithiasis. Extensive vascular calcification is present. No unexplained soft tissue calcifications or radiopaque foreign bodies.
